{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Radio Toolkit\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Some scripts for {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.reaper.fm"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
Reaper
}}}
 that I felt I needed for radio and podcast production.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Installation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 It's easiest to install Radio Toolkit using {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://reapack.com"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
ReaPack
}}}
. After installing it, find the ReaPack menu in Reaper, select {\f1 Import repositories...} and enter the following URL: {\f1 https://github.com/tomtjes/Radio-Toolkit/raw/master/index.xml}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Alternatively, feel free to download individual script and import them into Reaper, e.g. using the {\f1 Actions} list.\par}
}
